wikipedia_page.main: Arthur Lock Kemp (15 December 1868 – 1 March 1929) was an English cricketer who played first-class cricket in two matches for Middlesex, one each in 1890 and 1894. He was born at Kentish Town in London and died at Monken Hadley, Hertfordshire.
